cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes a framework for predicting kernelized classifiers in the visual domain, specifically for zero-shot learning of fine-grained categories from text descriptions. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper involves processing and utilizing unstructured text descriptions to generate classifiers for visual categories. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed approach involves optimization and embedding of class-level knowledge from the text domain as kernel classifiers in the visual domain, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper involves the use of AI techniques to predict classifiers for unseen visual classes from textual descriptions. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper proposes a distributional semantic kernel between text descriptions, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval tasks.
